  "text": "This answer identifies the five key C++ source files that define Chromium's multi-process architecture:\n\n1. **RenderProcessHostImpl** - Located in `content/browser/renderer_host/render_process_host_impl.h` (header) and `render_process_host_impl.cc` (implementation). This is the browser-side representation of a renderer process, managing the communication channel and resource allocation for each renderer process.\n\n2. **BrowserMainLoop** - Located in `content/browser/browser_main_loop.h` (header) and `browser_main_loop.cc` (implementation). This class orchestrates the main browser process event loop, initializing and managing all browser threads (UI thread, IO thread, etc.) and coordinating the startup and shutdown sequences.\n\n3. **RenderThreadImpl** - Located in `content/renderer/render_thread_impl.h` (header) and `render_thread_impl.cc` (implementation). This represents the main thread of a renderer process, where Blink WebView instances live and most renderer-side communication occurs via Mojo IPC.\n\n4. **ChildProcessLauncher** - Located in `content/browser/child_process_launcher.h` (header) and `child_process_launcher.cc` (implementation). This class is responsible for spawning child processes (renderer, GPU, utility processes) with proper sandboxing and initialization.\n\n5. **content.mojom.Renderer Interface** - Located in `content/common/renderer.mojom`. This is the primordial Channel-associated Mojo interface implemented by the renderer process, defining the browser-to-renderer control messages including methods for creating agent scheduling groups, transferring shared memory regions, and initializing the renderer with user agent data and other configuration.\n\nThese five components form the core of Chromium's multi-process architecture, enabling the browser process to manage, communicate with, and control renderer and other child processes."
}

